                     <note xml:lang="shn"/>
                     <note>Story a Bodhisatta who ate worms, as both his parents died when he was still a baby. His father died first, then his mother died soon afterwards. When his mother died, he didn't know it, he kept having breast milk from her dead mother until worms came out of his dead mother's breast and he continued to have the milk including the worms. As the house was far outside the village, no one knew about it. The story goes on to tell that the Baby had to eat the worms because his previous Karma, when he was a king, he asked others to eat worms.</note>
